meanings.definition: To earn more than someone else.
meanings.sent1: She outearns her brother by working extra hours.
meanings.sent2: He outearns his colleagues due to his successful business.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outearns the rabbit by collecting more nuts.
meanings.sent4: The student outearns the teacher in knowledge about dinosaurs.
meanings.sent5: The athlete outearns the competition with her speed and agility.

meanings.definition: To make more money than someone else.
meanings.sent1: My neighbor outearns me by working two jobs.
meanings.sent2: The CEO outearns all employees in the company.
meanings.sent3: The cat outearns the dog in treats by being extra cute.
meanings.sent4: The sun outearns the moon in brightness during the day.
meanings.sent5: The singer outearns other artists with her hit songs.
